      <body>
		<h1 style="text-align:center">THIS IS A CHEAT SHEET</h1> 
		<h1 style="text-align:center">FOR HTML5</h1> 
      <h1>All related to text</h1>
	  
	  
	  <h2>Formating</h2>
	  
	 <h3>Italic</h3>
		&ltem&gtYOUR TEXT&lt/em&gt = Italic <br>
		<b>OR</b> <br>
		&lti&gtYOUR TEXT&lt/i&gt <br>
		<b>For example:</b> <br>
		<em>(&ltem&gt)Maria(&lt/em&gt)</em> goes to the beach and get's lost.</p>
		
		<br> 
		
		<h3>Bold</h3>
        &ltstrong&gtYOUR TEXT&lt/strong&gt = Bold <br> 
		<b>OR</b> <br>
		&ltb&gtYOUR TEXT&lt/b&gt <br>
		<b>For example:</b> <br>
		<b>(&ltstrong&gt)Maria(&lt/strong&gt)</b> goes to the beach and get's lost.</p>
		<br>
		
		
	 <h2>Spacing</h2>
	  
	  <h3>Next Line</h3>
		&ltbr&gtYOUR TEXT = Next line <b>(No Spacing!!!)</b> <br>
		<b>For example:</b> <br>
		Maria goes to the beach (&ltbr&gt) <br>and get's lost.</p>
		
		&ltp&gtYOUR TEXT&ltp&gt = Next line <b>(With Spacing!!!)</b> <br>
		<b>For example:</b> <br>
		<p>(&ltp&gt)Thingy(&lt/p&gt) </p>
		Another Thingy
		
	<h2>Headers</h2>
	 
	 For headers you can use: &lth1&gt, &lth2&gt, &lth3&gt, &lth4&gt, ... <br>
	 <b>This goes only only until &lth6&gt, at &lth7&gt it appears as normal text!!!</b> <br>
	 <b>For example:</b> <br>
	 <h1 style="color :black;">(&lth1&gt)Header(&lt/h1&gt)</h1> <br>
	 <h2 style="color :black;">(&lth2&gt)Header(&lth2&gt) </h2> 
	
	  
		
     </body>
		
</html>
